<br><span style="font-family:Playwrite DE Grund;"><center>...</center></span>
<br><span style="font-family:Playwrite DE Grund;"><center>So you chose to say your piece. How bold. Although, it is understandable. Every human wishes for it. A prisoner in the tower of London scratched lines in the walls to count the passing days. A man climbed a hill, just to etch into a rock "this is very high". A monk lamented his boredom in a diary he hid under his bed for safekeeping. Each and every human has made their mark on this plane of existence, one way or another, exclaiming, "I do not wish to be forgotten. Please remember me."</center></span>
